Nigeria’s Vice-President, Yemi Osinbajo, has said only proactive leaders can solve the challenges affecting the country. This was contained in a statement signed by his spokesman, Laolu Osinbajo. Osinbajo made these remarkes on Monday, when he paid a courtesy visit to Abdulwasiu Lawal, Oniru of Iruland, in Lagos. “Our country needs all the leaders — the best leaders, the most proactive leaders, leaders prepared to bring the country together,” he said. Constitution Review: Nigeria needs proactive restructuring for peaceful coexistence – Osun Speaker “Lagos is a microcosm of Nigeria. Everybody is here. If things work out well here, things will be okay in the country. “I am sure your role here is that of someone who brings together communities — not just Yorubas, but everybody. “And I can see that from your choice of chiefs, you have gone to other parts, and I think this is the attitude of great leaders. “You should know that you are always in my prayers, because I believe that your role is crucial, not just for the development of this state, but for the whole country. “Today, you cannot relegate traditional rulers because of the exposure and education of those who occupy that position.” Bring an end to banditry, insecurity in Nigeria – Northern Govs tell IGP